{{Infobox cricket ground | ground = Cheden Holt | image = | caption = | location = [[Hambledon, Hampshire|Hambledon]], [[Hampshire]] | home club = [[Hambledon Club]] | county club = [[Hampshire county cricket teams|Hampshire]] | established = by 1776 | last used = 1776 }}
'''Cheden Holt''', situated on a hilltop about a mile from the rural village of [[Hambledon, Hampshire|Hambledon]] in [[Hampshire]], was a home venue of the [[Hambledon Club]]. It was used for a single important match in 1776, when [[Hampshire county cricket teams|a Hampshire side]] played [[Kent county cricket teams|a Kent team]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/2341_f.html First-Class Matches played on Cheden Holt, Hambledon]</ref> This is the only [[First-class cricket#Important matches classification|important match]] played at the ground, with no further mention of any other matches after 1776.
