{{Infobox venue | | stadium_name = USLS Coliseum | nickname = La Salle Coliseum | image = [[Image:La Salle Coliseum.jpg|220px|]] | caption = The arena [[facade|façade]] | location = [[Bacolod]], [[Negros Occidental]] | broke_ground = | opened = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[University of St. La Salle]] | operator = [[University of St. La Salle]] | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | tenants = [[Negros Slashers]] ([[Metropolitan Basketball Association|MBA]]) (1998–2002) | former_names = | seating_capacity = 8,000 }} The '''La Salle Coliseum''' is an indoor sporting [[arena]] located in [[Bacolod]], [[Philippines]].
The Coliseum has played host to a number of basketball games including those of [[Philippine Basketball Association]] out of town games and the now-defunct [[Metropolitan Basketball Association]], where it served as the home court of the [[Negros Slashers]].
It is the largest indoor facility in [[Negros Island Region]]. It is located inside the campus of the [[University of St. La Salle]] and hosts sporting and entertainment events in the province.
[[Negros Occidental Private Schools Sports Cultural Educational Association]] (NOPSSCEA) sports opening ceremony are usually held in the coliseum<ref>''Opening Ceremony,''[http://www.visayandailystar.com/2008/September/22/sportnews1.htm ''Visayan Daily Star''], September 22, 2008 edition</ref> and was the official venue during the [[2005 Southeast Asian Games]] particularly the [[Boxing at the 2005 Southeast Asian Games|Boxing]] event where 11 countries participated the competition. The coliseum also hosted two major karatedo championships, the 1996 [[Philippine Karatedo Federation]] National Championship headed by Pocholo Veguillas and Cristina Ramos-Jalasco, former [[Philippine Olympic Committee]] chairman and daughter of former president [[Fidel V. Ramos]] and the 2007 20th PKF National Open. Both tournaments were held at the USLS Coliseum. The tournaments were participated by hundreds of karatekas all over the country.<ref>''PKF and POF National Karatedo Winners,''[http://www.sunstar.com.ph/static/bac/2007/09/26/sports/jack.and.jill.karatekas.pocket.10.pof.medals.html Team Jack & Jill School] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090213030845/http://www.sunstar.com.ph/static/bac/2007/09/26/sports/jack.and.jill.karatekas.pocket.10.pof.medals.html |date=2009-02-13 }}, ''Sunstar'' September 26, 2007</ref><ref>''Karatedo Winners,''[http://www.visayandailystar.com/2007/September/17/sportnews4.htm NOKAF Karatedo], ''Visayan Daily Star'' September 17, 2007 edition</ref>
[[File:LaSalleColi.jpg|thumb|260px|Inside the La Sale Coliseum]]
