{{refimprove|date=July 2010}}
The '''Maloney''' is a gymnastics skill performed on the uneven bars by female gymnasts.  It is a transition skill from the low bar to the high bar.  When performing, the gymnast places her toes on the low bar and performs a sole circle before releasing from the bar into flight and catching the high bar.  The skill is named after the first gymnast to perform it at a World Championships or [[Olympic Games]], [[Kristen Maloney]].


