{{infobox country at games | CGA = MLT | CGAname = [[Malta Olympic Committee]] | games = Commonwealth Games | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.nocmalta.org }} | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = 50 | gold = 0 | silver = 1 | bronze = 4 | officials = | app_begin_year = 1958 | app_end_year = | seealso = }} [[Malta]] have competed at twelve [[Commonwealth Games]], making their debut in [[1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games|1958]]. They did not attend in [[1966 British Empire and Commonwealth Games|1966]], [[1974 British Commonwealth Games|1974]] or [[1978 Commonwealth Games|1978]], but have attended every Games since [[1982 Commonwealth Games|1982]]. Malta have won six medals at the Games, four of these in shooting.
