{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Oak Hill Cricket Club Ground | nickname = | country = Ireland | image = | location = [[County Wicklow]], [[Ireland]] | coord = {{coord|52.9286|-6.1022|display=inline}} | establishment = 2008 | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 2017 | club1 = [[Leinster Lightning]] | date = 15 July | year = 2018 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/5340.html Ground profile }}
'''Oak Hill Cricket Club Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[County Wicklow]], [[Leinster]], [[Ireland]].
==History== The ground was constructed in 2008 by businessman Peter Savill on his [[stud farm]] at [[Dunganstown]].<ref name="NEWS1">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.ie/regionals/wicklowpeople/news/millionaires-dream-brings-topclass-cricket-to-wicklow-27839946.html|title=Millionaire's dream brings top-class cricket to Wicklow|date=26 June 2008|work=[[Irish Independent]]|accessdate=15 July 2018|location=Dublin}}</ref> The ground was officially opened on 22 June 2008, with an Ireland XI playing a [[Lashings World XI|Lashings XI]].<ref name="NEWS1"/> The [[cricket pavilion|pavilion]] at the ground is an exact replica of the one found at [[Ampleforth College]] in [[England]], where Savill was educated.<ref name="NEWS1"/> [[First-class cricket]] was first played at the ground in 2012, when [[Ireland cricket team|Ireland]] played [[South Africa A cricket team|South Africa A]].<ref name="FCM">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/5340_f.html|title=First-Class Matches played on Oak Hill Cricket Club|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> The ground was scheduled to host two [[Twenty20]] matches as part of the tour, however both matches were cancelled due to rain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/5340_tt.html|title=Twenty20 Matches played on Oak Hill Cricket Club|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/439/439349.html|title=Ireland v South Africa A, 2012|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> The future of the ground was called into question in 2013, when residents of a neighbouring property took legal action in the [[High Court (Ireland)|High Court]] after complaining about excess noise from the venue.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/courts/international-cricket-grounds-future-uncertain-after-noise-dispute-with-neighbours-29236214.html|title=International cricket ground's future uncertain after noise dispute with neighbours|date=1 May 2013|work=Irish Independent|accessdate=15 July 2018|location=Dublin}}</ref> The ground hosted a first-class match between [[Leinster Lightning]] and [[North West Warriors]] in [[2017 Inter-Provincial Championship]], which was the inaugural domestic first-class match to be played in Leinster.<ref name="FCM"/>
==Records== ===First-class=== * '''Highest team total:''' 365 by [[Leinster Lightning]] v [[North West Warriors]], 2017<ref name="INTERPRO">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/1027/1027103.html|title=Leinster Lightning v North West Warriors, 2017|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> * '''Lowest team total:''' 202 by [[Ireland cricket team|Ireland]] v [[South Africa A cricket team|South Africa A]], 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/439/439344.html|title=Ireland v South Africa A, 2012|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> * '''Highest individual innings:''' 156 by [[Ed Joyce]] for Leinster Lightning v North West Warriors, 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/5340/f_Centuries.html|title=Oak Hill Cricket Club, Oak Hill - Centuries in first-class cricket|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> * '''Best bowling in an innings:''' 7-56 by [[Wayne Parnell]] for South Africa A v Ireland, 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/60/5340/f_Most_Wickets_in_Innings.html|title=Oak Hill Cricket Club, Oak Hill - Seven Wickets in an Innings in first-class cricket|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> * '''Best bowling in a match:''' 8-120 by [[George Dockrell]] for Leinster Lightning v North West Warriors, 2017<ref name="INTERPRO"/>
