'''Robleh Ali Adou''' (born 17 June 1964) is an international [[windsurfing|windsurfer]] who competes for [[Djibouti]].

Adou has competed in three Olympic Games, firstly he was at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]] where he competed in the [[Sailing at the 1988 Summer Olympics – Men's Division II|Division II Class]], he finished in 40th place overall, four years later he entered the [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics – Men's Lechner A-390|Lechner A-390 Class]] where this time he finished in 39th place. his final appearance at the Olympics was in the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics – Men's Mistral One Design|Mistral One Class]], there he finished in 46th place.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/al/robleh-ali-adou-1.html Sports Reference Profile]</ref>

