'''Vaterpolo klub Budva''' (formerly '''SD VK Mogren''' between 1946 and 1992, '''PVK Budvanska Rivijera''' between 1992 and 2008<ref>http://www.vkbudva.com/o-klubu.html</ref>) is a [[water polo]] club in [[Budva]], [[Montenegro]]. It takes part in the [[Montenegrin Water Polo Cup]]. In 2008 VK Budva started to participate in [[The Adriatic Water Polo League]]. Budva also played in Final four of Water Polo Euroleague in 2011 and finished 4th. Budva participate in Montenegrin Water Polo league along with PVK Jadran Herceg Novi and VK Primorac Kotor.
